Product Information
Federal Premium products Federal Premium Personal Defense HST Ammunition has been specially designed to deliver consistent, tremendous expansion, optimum penetration and superior terminal performance. The specially designed hollow point will not plug while passing through a variety of barriers and the jacket and core hold together providing nearly 100% weight retention! This ammunition was engineered to meet or exceed FBI ammunition testing protocols; these protocols put bullets through 10% ordinance gelatin, steel, wallboard, plywood, laminated automobile safety glass and gelatin covered in heavy clothing and measure how well the bullets penetrate, expand and hold together. 

Extensive testing has shown that the on average the 9mm Luger load will deliver 13.63" of penetration, 0.63" of expansion, 90% weight retention through all FBI barriers when shot through a Glock 17 at 10 feet. 

One of the great things about this ammunition are high quality features that make this ammunition perfect choice for self-defense ammunition. Each round of ammunition is loaded into a Federal Premium nickel plated brass case with waterproofing on the case mouth and primer. Every load has a consistent powder charge and reliable primer for consistent ignition. Every HST bullet features a tapered jacket profile for reliable feeding, a cannelure that locks the copper jacket to the lead core, patented co-aligned internal and external skiving and a deep tapered hollow point that will not clog. 

Technical Information
Caliber: 9mm Luger
Bullet Weight: 124 Grains
Bullet Style: HST Jacketed Hollow Point
Case Type: Nickel Plated Brass


Ballistics Information

This ammunition was engineered to meet or exceed FBI ammunition testing protocols; these protocols put bullets through 10% ordinance gelatin, steel, wallboard, plywood, laminated automobile safety glass and gelatin covered in heavy clothing and measure how well the bullets penetrate, expand and hold together. 

Extensive testing has shown that the on average the 9mm Luger load will deliver 13.63" of penetration, 0.63" of expansion, 90% weight retention through all FBI barriers when shot through a Glock 17 at 10 feet. 

One of the great things about this ammunition are high quality features that make this ammunition perfect choice for self-defense ammunition. Each round of ammunition is loaded into a Federal Premium nickel plated brass case with waterproofing on the case mouth and primer. Every load has a consistent powder charge and reliable primer for consistent ignition. Every HST bullet features a tapered jacket profile for reliable feeding, a cannelure that locks the copper jacket to the lead core, patented co-aligned internal and external skiving and a deep tapered hollow point that will not clog.

title: For Sale:  SKS Tapco gas tube
postcontent:
***SOLD***

If you want to put a synthetic stock with a pistol grip/collapsible stock on your SKS, you'll need enough US-made parts to make it 922r compliant. For the SKS, that means you need 7 parts - 3 come from whatever stock you use, 3 come from most detachable magazines, which leaves you needing one more. That's where this gas tube comes in: it counts as the 7th part, which makes your sporterized SKS nice and legal.

I have the Intrafuse stock for sale along with four Tapco 20-round mags for sale as well - check my other listings. If you want to buy the whole set, we can work out a deal.

title: For Sale:  Winchester M-53 25-20 WCF in Very Good Condition
location: West Virginia, West Virginia, United States
postcontent: This listing is for a Winchester Model 53,This rifle has been restored to excellent condition using the slow rust blue technique of metal finishing. This type of finish has proven to be the most rugged of all traditional finishes as the finish is in the metal not just on it. This is why some older Winchesters will have virtually all the blue on the barrel while other parts of the gun seem to be more worn. It's because the barrel was rust blued at the Winchester factory. Craftsmen of the day guarded their formulas and techniques very closely for it was a source of great pride to be able to apply such a beautiful and lasting finish to a fine firearm. This little gun was built in 1927 and is ready for the next 100 years of service. I have taken many pictures to help show the condition. The only flaw would be a repaired crack in the stock forward of the bottom butt plate screw. This repair is very solid but needs to be mentioned for proper representation of the item. All screws are very good. Bore is mirror bright. I have shot squirrels with this little gun and can tell you it's truly delightful to shoot and the ammunition really isn't that expensive. This is a very accurate gun that should bring years of pleasure. Please e-mail with any questions.

Daniel Defense’s new caliber option, the 300 Blackout, was originally designed to give the shooter a 30 caliber projectile which could be fired out of the AR platform without an increase in magazine size while still utilizing a standard bolt.
